@asmeurer your blog says:
> that no computer algebra system has ever completely implemented all the parts of it (Risch algorithm).

Is that the case even now(considering that you wrote the blog post ~7 years ago)?

@asmeurer 
> You can sometimes trick it into working with $$\sqrt{x}$$ by manually creating an extension for $$e^{\frac{1}{2}\log(x)}$$

...but if I didn't make the extension `manually`, I can trust it to be transcendental, and trust the answer
